<section xml:id="sec-section-name2" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Section Title</title>

  <p> A <term>pulse</term> is a single, non-repeating disturbance that propagates through space and time, transferring energy and momentum.</p>
  <p> A <term>wave</term> is a continuous, periodic succession of pulses.</p>
  <image source="wave-driver-1.png">  </image>
  <p>
    So the integral <m> \int_0^2 3x(x^2+1) \, dx = 18 </m>
    <md>
      \frac{d}{dx} \int_1^x \frac{1}{t}\, dt = \frac{1}{x}
    </md>
    <md>
      \int_a^b f(x)\, dx = F(b) - F(a)
    </md>
  </p>
